const headHtml = "<title>BIN Sniping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</title>\n    <meta name=\"description\" content=\"An expert based BIN sniping guide for Hypixel SkyBlock explaining how to spot real price gaps, avoid fake wins, use live references correctly and decide when sniping is worth the effort.\">\n    <link rel=\"canonical\" href=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/bin-sniping-guide-2026\">\n\n    <meta property=\"og:url\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/bin-sniping-guide-2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:type\" content=\"article\">\n    <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"BIN Sniping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026\">\n    <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"Learn how BIN sniping still works in 2026: faster recognition, cleaner references and better judgment about whether a listing will actually resell.\">\n    <meta property=\"og:image\" content=\"https://notenoughcoins.net/static/NEC.png\">\n    <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n      {\n        \"@context\": \"https://schema.org\",\n        \"@type\": \"BlogPosting\",\n        \"headline\": \"BIN Sniping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026\",\n        \"description\": \"Expert based guide to BIN sniping, price recognition and fast AH decision-making in Hypixel SkyBlock.\",\n        \"datePublished\": \"2026-02-16\",\n        \"dateModified\": \"2026-04-18\",\n        \"author\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"NotEnoughCoins\"\n        },\n        \"publisher\": {\n          \"@type\": \"Organization\",\n          \"name\": \"Coflnet GmbH\"\n        },\n        \"url\": \"https://notenoughcoins.net/guides/bin-sniping-guide-2026\"\n      }\n    </script>";
const bodyHtml = "<main>\n      <div class=\"site-shell article-layout\">\n        <article class=\"article\">\n          <a class=\"article-meta\" href=\"/guides#months-list\">2026-02-16 • AH Flipping</a>\n          <h1>BIN Sniping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</h1>\n          <p class=\"lede\">BIN sniping still works, but only if you stop treating it like a blind refresh contest. The strongest snipers are not just fast. They recognize item families instantly, know what modifiers change the resale, and can tell the difference between a real underpriced listing and a future relist burden. The method is speed-sensitive, but recognition is what keeps it profitable.</p>\n\n          <div class=\"note\">\n            <strong>Primary source base:</strong> kiutn's AH flipping overview, fightBck's auction flipping guide and the creator discussions that place BIN sniping next to normal flipping and lowballing rather than treating it as a magic shortcut.\n          </div>\n\n          <h2>A real snipe has to fit a believable resale band</h2>\n          <p>A cheap number alone is not enough. If the next real listing is barely higher, if the item has weak demand, or if the cheapest page is already stale, the snipe is probably just a slower flip with more pressure attached to it. The best catches are obvious because the listing is clearly misplaced relative to active prices and the resale band still looks clean after taxes.</p>\n          <p>This is why smaller market specialization matters. Players who know one item family well can evaluate stars, enchant combinations, pets or utility gear much faster than players trying to snipe everything at once. A narrow edge beats random speed almost every time.</p>\n\n          <h2>Recognition beats refresh spam</h2>\n          <p>Most weak sniping sessions look busy but produce little. Players refresh constantly, chase every highlighted gap and make valuation mistakes because they are solving the item from zero each time. Good sniping looks calmer. You know what you are searching, which modifiers matter, and where you are willing to pass. That keeps your clicks focused and your mistakes cheaper.</p>\n          <p>It also keeps sniping in the right role. In 2026, public tools shortened the life of obvious mistakes, so BIN sniping makes the most sense as one layer in a wider money routine rather than your only income plan.</p>\n\n          <h2>Use tools as reference compression</h2>\n          <p>The right live tools make BIN sniping faster by doing the first comparison work for you. <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flipper\">SkyCofl AH flipper</a> is the cleanest free reference for modifier-aware underpriced listings, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">top movers</a> warns when a category is unstable, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/lowSupply\">low supply</a> surfaces thin markets, <a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/subscriptions\">notifier subscriptions</a> push candidates into Discord, and <a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/auction-flips\">BazaarPro auction flips</a> wraps the workflow in saved filters. None of these tools remove the final judgment call. They only help you reach it before the opportunity disappears.</p>\n\n          <h2>When BIN sniping is worth your time</h2>\n          <p>BIN sniping is strongest when you already understand normal AH flipping and want occasional high-confidence catches without doing full lowballing. If you do not yet understand taxes, resale discipline and item liquidity, sniping becomes an expensive way to learn the same lesson under more time pressure. Build the foundation first, then use sniping as a speed layer on top of it.</p>\n\n          <h2>Read next</h2>\n          <ul class=\"related-list\">\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/ah-flipping-guide-2026\">Auction House Flipping Guide for Hypixel SkyBlock in 2026</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/lowballing-and-flip-discovery\">Lowballing and Flip Discovery in Hypixel SkyBlock</a></li>\n            <li><a href=\"/guides/market-literacy-margin-volume-risk\">How to Read Margin, Volume and Risk Before You Flip</a></li>\n          </ul>\n        </article>\n\n        <aside class=\"article-aside\">\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best paired tools</h3>\n            <ul class=\"tool-list\">\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/flipper\">SkyCofl AH flipper</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/topMovers\">SkyCofl top movers</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/lowSupply\">SkyCofl low supply</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/recentFlips\">SkyCofl recent flips</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://sky.coflnet.com/subscriptions\">SkyCofl notifiers</a></li>\n              <li><a href=\"https://pro.skyblock.bz/features/auction-flips\">BazaarPro auction flips</a></li>\n            </ul>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Best for</h3>\n            <p>Players with a narrow item specialty who want fast opportunities on top of a more stable main money method.</p>\n          </div>\n          <div>\n            <h3>Source videos</h3>\n            <p>The creator material is strongest when it treats sniping as price recognition work instead of a casino-style refresh routine.</p>\n          </div>\n        </aside>\n      </div>\n    </main>";
